# User instructions (all projects)

These are language-agnostic, project-agnostic rules. Language-specific rules
live in `~/.claude/rules/<lang>.md` and load only when relevant files are touched.

## Style

- Never use em dashes (`--`, `---`, or Unicode `—`). Use a hyphen `-` or rewrite the sentence.
- Prefer clear, specific writing over filler. Avoid hype adjectives/adverbs (bold,
  brutal, honest, quietly, seamless, ...) that add tone but no information; cut them or
  state the concrete fact instead. Headers are plain labels, no parentheticals.

## Working conventions

- Match the surrounding code: naming, comment density, and idioms of the file being edited.
- Raise descriptive, named exceptions rather than bare/generic ones, in any language.
- Keep changes minimal and scoped to the task; do not refactor unrelated code.
- Do not commit, push, or perform other outward-facing actions unless asked.

## Per-repo instructions

Most repos keep their canonical instructions in `.github/copilot-instructions.md`
(and sometimes `AGENTS.md`). Claude only auto-loads `CLAUDE.md`, so each repo
should have a `CLAUDE.md` that imports the existing file:

    @.github/copilot-instructions.md

That keeps a single source of truth shared with other tools.
